author: Associated Press
title: 2 Georgia men accused of selling phony LSU-Florida tickets
text:
By Associated Press Related Articles Student arrested in alleged shooting threat at Ga college Wanted Buford man arrested on drugs, weapons charges Former Falcons running back arrested for DUI in Hall Co. Hall Co. authorities arrest suspect in recent Lanier Islands shooting 
BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) LSU police arrested two Georgia men peddling phony tickets to Saturday's LSU football game after disappointed fans reported the forgeries to university officials. The Advocate reports 30-year-old Kenny Lamar Redding and 29-year-old Christopher Harrison, both of Atlanta, were booked on two counts each of an offense against intellectual property. Police say Harrison, who was identified by the victims as the man who sold them the counterfeit tickets, was also booked on two counts of theft. Both men maintained their innocence when questioned by LSU police. Harrison and Redding remain in East Baton Rouge Parish Prison Monday. Bail has not yet been set.
